{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-0143"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Camelid-Raising Operations Coordination"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "0143"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :agriculture/camelid-raising
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:animal-welfare :food-security :rural-employment]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :camelid-facility-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :audit-ledger]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:telemetry :optimization :dmn :bpmn]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "CamelOpsAdvisor ⊣ Camelid Facility Operations Governor, langgraph-clj
 StateGraph (langgraph.graph, camelops.operation/build), append-only
 audit ledger (camelops.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore). Fixes
 a prior deferred-stub + fake-dependency combo: `deps.edn`'s top-level
 `:deps` was literally `{}` -- the real `io.github.kotoba-lang/langgraph`
 dependency only existed under the unused `:dev :override-deps` alias,
 so no build that actually ran (`clojure -M:run`/`:test`, no `:dev`)
 ever had langgraph on the classpath. `operation.cljc`'s own docstring
 explicitly said \"langgraph-clj StateGraph integration is deferred...
 This stub version [...] defines the high-level flow synchronously\" and
 hand-rolled `run-operation` instead of using the real API -- yet this
 blueprint still claimed `:itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented`. No
 audit ledger existed anywhere in the repo, and there was no CI
 workflow. Now: a genuinely compiled StateGraph (`:intake -> :advise ->
 :govern -> :decide -+-> :commit / :request-approval -> :commit /
 :hold`) with `interrupt-before #{:request-approval}` + in-memory
 checkpointer for real human-in-the-loop resume, and a real
 `camelops.store/ledger` + `append-ledger!` (new in this fix -- no
 ledger existed before) genuinely wired into the `:commit`, `:hold`,
 and `:request-approval` (rejection) graph nodes. `camelops.advisor`'s
 CamelOpsAdvisor, `camelops.governor`'s Camelid Facility Operations
 Governor (facility registration, closed op allowlist, treatment/
 slaughter-blocked, herd-count/fiber-yield plausibility, cost-threshold
 escalation, always-escalate health concerns), `camelops.phase`'s 0->3
 rollout gate (phase-0 forces every otherwise-committable proposal
 through human approval, never an autonomous commit), and
 `camelops.registry`/`camelops.facts`'s pure domain checks are ALL
 reused UNCHANGED -- this fix only wires the existing camelid-raising
 domain policy into a real compiled graph and a real ledger, it does not
 redesign it. Proven end-to-end by `test/camelops/operation_test.cljc`
 (ledger stays empty until a real commit or across an interrupted/
 not-yet-approved run, hold-until-approved for the always-escalating
 health-concern flag and a high-cost supply order, governor rejection
 blocks commit for five independent HARD violations -- unregistered
 facility, treatment/slaughter block, non-positive herd count, negative
 fiber yield -- phase-0 forces human approval even for an otherwise-
 clean proposal) through the REAL compiled graph, plus a
 `clojure -M:dev:run` demo runner producing real ledger entries for
 every scenario. 47 tests / 153 assertions green (`clojure
 -M:dev:test`), clj-kondo 0 errors/0 warnings. CI
 (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`, sibling-checkout pattern for `:local/root`
 deps) was missing and is added in this fix."}
